            "http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4094/4932377546_fe8f237379.jpg"
        ],
        "post": " 西尾中華そばSorry for the lack of updates lately.  I was living at hotel resorts for a summer camp job in decidedly ramen lacking areas of Japan.Here's Nishio's summertime special.Ice cold, literally.  The addition of a scoop of slushy broth keeps things temperature controlled.  Other additions are a scoop of what tasted like Hawaiian poke and some brightly colored peppers.Nishio is in my top 10.  Good vibe, cool owner, and excellent shoyu ramen.  Go if you have a chance.September is going to be an interesting month for ramen.  Can a long distance backpacker survive on ramen and energy bars for a week?  Stay tuned.  ",
        "title": " 夏のラーメン (Summer Ramen at Nishio) "
    },
    {
        "date": "2010-08-09 00:00:00",
        "pictures": [
            "http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4075/4877309417_9cf40d6f92.jpg",
            "http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4120/4877334449_ef3a7ff28d.jpg",
            "http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4081/4877326001_e969f3d7ac.jpg",
