        "post": " えん寺Enji finds itself in just about every magazine on the shelves.  Ramen magazines, of course, but also in all the weekly magazines.  What's a weekly magazine?  Let's just say they're not for kids.Yet another in the tonkotsu gyokai tsukemen field.  Enji sets itself apart by using a secret vegetable paste in their soup, along with pork, chicken, fish, and even some shrimp.  The darker than average noodles match perfectly.I like the use of a bamboo screen in the bowl.  Soggy bottom noodles are no fun.If you're adventurous, the shop recommends a little habanero spice powder.  It ads some serious kick, obviously.  If you can read Japanese, you are warned of this fact.  If you don't, you'll learn the hard way.Supleks DatabaseView Larger Map  ",
        "title": " えん寺 (Enji in Koenji) "
