        "post": " うまか軒    The Kumamoto airport is a bad place to get a bowl of ramen.    Overcooked is a bad way to serve eggs.    Fried garlic can sometimes fix a bad bowl.    Sometimes not.  And the iPod camera is a bad way to document your ramen travels.    The flight from Kumamoto to Tokyo is awesome.  It follows the coast, from Hiroshima to Osaka to Kyoto to Tokyo.  Don't eat ramen at an airport.    ",
