        "post": " 破顔    This bowl was actually another outing with the local Mormons.  What better way to console the losing side of the recent American presidential election than with a nice bowl of soupless noodles!    Hagan is very highly rated in the magazines and online.  They offer a regular ramen, but do yourself a favor and get their signature 汁なし.  The flame broiled bits of pork are fantastic.     Little bits of dried fish and some heavy soy tare blend perfectly.  Free omori size at lunch time, but the regular was big enough for me.    Official Site   View Larger Map    東京都練馬区桜台1-5-11 Tokyo, Nerima-ku, Sakuradai 1-5-11 Closest station: Sakuradai  Open 11:30-14:00, 18:30-12:30 Sundays 11:00-about 5:00 Closed Mondays  ",
