        ],
        "post": " Mister Donuts    Simply eaten because it sits in my ramen bucket list. No expectations. Scratch that . . . low expectations.    Mister Donuts is a nationwide chain of donut shops. The cheap ones are about a buck, and premium ones not much more than that. I have been here hundreds of times, as they give free refills on their tasty cafe au lait.  And for some reason, they serve a very limited menu of Chinese food; noodles and dumplings.    The ramen . . . not bad! I'm sure the kakuni topping was preserved in an airlock bag and shipped from some far off place, and I'm sure the soup was from a bottle of concentrated brown liquid. But it wasn't awful. I'll just leave it at that.    About six bucks for the ramen, donut, and coffee.    This place is everywhere, and the hours are all a bit different.  Official Site Here  ",
