        ],
        "post": " 弘富    Highly ranked ramen in Hachioji is always dominated by En. No one else even stands a chance.    If gold is out of your reach, why not go for silver? Hirotomi is definitely a contender. Hachioji-style, rich shoyu with a lot of onions, might as well be called Hirotomi-style.    At only 800 yen for the chashumen, this place is a steal.    Check it out a few minutes walk down the tracks, in the opposite direction of En.     View Larger Map   東京都八王子市明神町3-11 Tokyo, Hachioji-shi, Myojincho 3-11 Closest station: Hachioji  Open 11:00-19:30 Closed Sundays  ",
