        "post": " やよいそば 角店    I asked the cop where Yayoisoba was, and he just pointed at the sign for Yayoi bridge. Makes sense!    This shop came recommended by a few ramen connoisseurs. Spot on, this was a great bowl. Look how black that soup is. Beautiful.    Melt-in-your-mouth chashu, deep broth, and the noodles matched well. The soup is less fishy than other Takayama shops, though just by a little.    Apologies for the weak photos from the Takayama set. The DSLR was out of batteries and I was forced to use my iPad. Yes, I was one of those guys taking photos with an iPad. I won't make that mistake again.    Official Site Here    岐阜県高山市七日町1-43 Gifu-ken, Takayama-shi, Nanukamachi 1-43 Closest station: Takayama  Open 11:00-19:00 Closed Tuesdays  ",
