        "post": " けやき    Hiroo is home to some of the most prominent embassies, and therefore one of the wealthier parts of town. The little bistros in the area are excellent, as they probably cater to Europeans with sophisticated palates. Rare imported cheeses, fine wine, all that jazz. And then there is this ramen shop. Next to the Lamborghini dealer.    An easy to read English menu, as expected.    And a poor bowl, as expected.  Would an excellent ramen shop be popular with the upper-crust expat community? Probably not.      東京都港区南麻布5-10 Tokyo, Minato-ku, Minami Azabu 5-10 Closest station: Hiroo  Open ??  ",
