        "post": " 麺屋 参壱    I decided to hit up any ramen shop I could find on the 45 minute bicycle ride between my apartment and somewhere in Setagaya. And Sanichi had an air around it that beckoned to be sampled.    Spicy miso ramen? Sure, why not.    A tasty gyoza-set to go with it? Sure, why not.    Garlicky.    Also garlicky. Apologies for my fuzzy memory, but this place didn't really register.      東京都世田谷区上北沢4-30-8 Tokyo, Setagaya-ku, Kamikitazawa 4-30-8 Closest station: Kamikitazawa  Open 11:30-15:00, 18:00-25:00  ",
