        "post": " 麺鮮醤油房 周平    According to the internet, Shuhei is one of the best ramen shops in Ehime Prefecture's capital city of Matsuyama. And for the lucky traveler with a Toyoko Inn point card (Japan's premier budget hotel chain), this shop is just a minute away.    Homemade noodles in a fragrant shoyu soup are the draw here. The shop uses a super high quality soy sauce from local Kajita Shoten brewery, and you'll be hit with that impact on the first sip.    Decent bowl, open late, what's not to love in this quiet corner of Japan?    Official Site Here      愛媛県松山市一番町2丁目4-11 Ehime-ken, Matsuyama-shi, Ichibancho 2-4-11 Closest station: Okaido  Open 11:30-14:30, 17:30-2:00am Closed Sundays  ",
