        "post": " 横浜家    Some big chain. Maybe it is near a station. We were driving, so I can't be sure. Feel free to do your own research on this one. Searching for 横浜家 on the net brings up a million results, as 横浜家 just means Yokohama Shop.    Can you tell which direction this review is going?    At least I learned a new Japanese phrase. 盛り放題, morihodai, ice cream means you can stack as much on your cone as you want. I should have stuck with the ice cream.    Whoever gets suckered into being the shop master for the day gets their photo put up on the board in the front. Would a different portrait produce a different bowl?      Probably not.    Address: I didn't check. Somewhere on some main road in Kanagawa, maybe. Hours: Probably 24/7 Nearest station: I dunno Website: Probably this one.  ",
