        "post": " ら・けいこ    Walking back to the hotel, literally on the same block as the last spot I slurped, was an unassuming hole in the wall that caught my eye. The menu, located on the street, had just two choices; with or without soup. Rakeiko calls themselves a スープ無専門店, a soupless noodle specialty shop, so it was a no-brainer.    Simple; just fat, carbs, and salt.    The only thing it was missing was a nice, runny egg on top. By the way, the above shot is half-sized noodles, a request I made. Being a Jiro-inspired shop, you can expect a voluminous mass as standard.  Also, ninniku irimasu ka?    I left very happy, and very satisfied.      愛知県名古屋市中区栄4-12-6 Aichi-ken, Nagoya-shim Chuo-ku, Sakae 4-12-6 Closest station: Sakae  Open 11:00-15:00, 18:00-21:00 Closed Sundays  ",
