        "post": " rabo    Anaya, a heavy bowl just a few minutes south of my apartment recently opened a spinoff shop a few minutes north of my apartment. Convenient!    This bowl of ramen, in a shop down a little alley, will most likely be missed by most due to the location, but shouldn't be. Simple and unassuming, it is a great blend of chicken, pork, and niboshi.  A simple review for a simple shop. If you are in the area, pop on in for a slurp.      東京都渋谷区本町4-13-10 Tokyo, Shibuya-ku, Honmachi 4-13-10 Closest station: Nishi-Shinjuku-Gochome  Open 11:30-15:00, 17:30-22:00 Closed Sundays  ",
