        "post": " The most popular restaurant ranking site in Japan released an official Top 50 Ramen list in 2016. Here they are, with links to the ones I have visited. I have bolded shops that are in my book.  道 - Michi - Tokyo(I went! Post coming soon) 和 dining 清乃 - Seino - Wakayama 一燈 - Itto - Tokyo 八雲 - Yakumo - Tokyo 饗 くろ喜 - Motenashi Kuroki - Tokyo 和海 - Nagomi - Hyogo(I went! Post coming soon) こうかいぼう - Kokaibo - Tokyo 鶏喰 - Trick - Kanagawa(I went! Post coming soon) 中華そば屋 伊藤 - Ito - Tokyo 煮干鰮らーめん 圓 - En - Tokyo 麺処 晴 - Haru - Tokyo 麺屋 丈六 - Joroku - Osaka 金田家 - Kanadaya - Fukuoka 麺尊RAGE - Tokyo ラーメン家 みつ葉 - Mitsuba - Nara 麺屋 NOROMA - Nara(I went! Post coming soon) 金色不如帰 - Hototogisu - Tokyo 田中商店 - Tanakashoten - Tokyo らぁ麺やまぐち - Yamaguchi - Tokyo しば田 - Shibata - Tokyo 大和 - Yamato - Tochigi イチカワ - Ichikawa - Ibaraki 中華そば　よしかわ - Yoshikawa - Saitama ラーメン 巌哲 - Gantetsu - Tokyo 煮干しつけ麺　宮元 - Miyamoto - Tokyo 和心 武庫之荘店 - Nagomi Mukonosu - Hyogo むさし野 - Musashino - Chiba 蘭鋳 - Ranchu - Tokyo 多賀野 - Tagano - Tokyo うえまち - Uemachi - Osaka らぁ麺 すぎ本 - Sugimoto - Tokyo 伊吹 - Ibuki - Tokyo らーめん工房 龍 - Ryu - Fukuoka ようすけ - Yosuke - Tochigi 麺屋 極鶏 - Gokei - Kyoto 麺屋 彩未 - Saimi - Hokkaido らーめん鱗 西中島店 - Uroko Nishinakajima - Osaka 麺や而今 - Jikon - Osaka らーめん 弥七 - Yashichi - Osaka 麺処 きなり - Kinari - Tokyo 無法松 - Muhomatsu - Fukuoka とみ田 - Tomita - Chiba 豚星 - Butaboshi - Kanagawa 彩色ラーメン きんせい夢風 - Kinsemufu - Osaka らぁ麺屋　飯田商店 - Idashoten - Kanagawa 進化 - Shinka - Tokyo 燦燦斗 - Sansanto - Tokyo 南京ラーメン 黒門 - Kuromon - Fukuoka 四つ葉 - Yotsuba - Saitama Japanese Soba Noodles 蔦 - Tsuta - Tokyo   The original list can be found over at the Tabelog site.    I like this list. Personally, it gives me a solid selection of Osaka and Fukuoka shops to check out this year, as well as a few more in Tokyo that I haven't been to. Goals in life are good.    This list isn't a direct representation of Tabelog's user base. Tabelog operates on a 5 star system, and is purely based on user's ratings. Generally, anything with more than 4 stars is considered an amazing restaurant. In my dealings with food of all types, this is normally true. But, if you look at the flat out rankings, some shops that are in the general top 10 for ramen, such as Orenoramen Apare, aren't in this list of 50 at all. I'm not sure who curated this list, but I would love to know their reasons for leaving off the shop that I consider my favorite in Japan. And Tsuta, despite their Michelin star and high numerical score, looks to have been snidely added at the very bottom.    I was also really happy that this list re-ignited memories of some of my old favorites. In the search for ramen, we sometimes neglect some shops after visiting once. Number 28, Ranchu, is a perfect example . . . and it's only a 10 minute bicycle ride from my house.    46 / 50 is almost there. Wish me luck!          ",
        "title": " Best 50 Ramen Shops According to Tabelog "
    },
